# To make it work

- `hdmi-unplug` is the actual service script and shall be placed into the `/usr/local/bin/` directory.
- `hdmi-unplug.service` is file for `systemd` and shall be placed into the `/etc/systemd/system/` directory.
- Run `sudo systemctl enable hdmi-unplug.service`.

> **Note**: Please adopt variables and parameters to your own laptop setup.

When you change your `hdmi-unplug.sevice` file or your `hdmi-unplug` script - it is good to run `sudo systemctl daemon-reload` command to apply changes.
